{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>Prohormone convertases (PCs) 1 and 2 are a family of eukaryotic subtilisins thought to mediate the proteolytic cleavage of many peptide precursors [[cite:PUB00071624]]. Protein 7B2 (secretogranin V) functions as a molecular chaperone for PC2, preventing its premature activation in the regulated secretory pathway [[cite:PUB00071626]]. 7B2 represents a potent inhibitor of PC2, and it is also required for the activation of PC2, which is synthesised as a zymogen. Protein 7B2 has an N-terminal activation domain and a C-terminal (CT) inhibitory domain (MEROPS inhibitor family I21), separated by a furin cleavage site [[cite:PUB00014512]]. 7B2 is synthesised as a precursor protein that is cleaved into the N-terminal fragment and the C-terminal peptide [[cite:PUB00071625]].</p>\n\n<p>7B2 has been linked to neurodegenerative diseases. It may act as an anti-aggregation chaperone [[cite:PUB00093454]]. However, in an APP model mouse 7B2 knockout has been shown to reduce rather than enhance plaque burden [[cite:PUB00093453]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure nil, :overlaps-with nil, :member-databases {"pfam" {"PF05281" "Neuroendocrine protein 7B2 precursor (Secretogranin V)"}, "panther" {"PTHR12738" "NEUROENDOCRINE PROTEIN 7B2"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "Neuroendocrine 7B2 precursor", "short" "Secretogranin_V"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 0, "domain_architectures" 17, "proteomes" 967, "taxa" 3814, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 1892, "sets" 0, "proteins" 1775, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 1204}, "pathways" 0}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {}, :set-info nil, :accession "IPR007945", :literature {"PUB00071624" {"URL" nil, "issue" "1-2", "authors" ["Seidah NG" "Chretien M."], "ISO_journal" "Brain Res.", "DOI_URL" "http://dx.doi.org/10.1016/S0006-8993(99)01909-5", "medline_journal" 